<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.852/13</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>779. Replying No. 1644, 7th April. For Phelps Bros, [from
                            Austro-Americana]:</p>
                        <p>Approve your action for our boats. You have authority together with
                            Buenos Aires without referring any more to us to sell best possible all
                            our other steamers, namely <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName>Martha</persName>, Virginia, <persName>Laura</persName>,
                                    <persName>Alice</persName></hi>. Instruct our captains to
                            cooperate fully with you. Provide for them, officers, and whole crew
                            adequate board and continue payments as heretofore unless you secure
                            them adequate employment. Cable name of European bankers who will pay
                            us. Working on Tripcovich, Atlantica, and Orient steamers and cabling
                            later [regarding] Austro-Americana crew.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>